  "prompt": "If I am talking on whatsapp call to someone and another person calls me on my whatsapp. what status will he get. will it show busy?",
  "response": "Yes, the person calling you on WhatsApp while you're already on a WhatsApp call will likely see one of the following:\n\n*   **Ringing (for a short time):** Their call might initially ring briefly.\n*   **Call Ended/Not Answered:** If you don't decline it and keep talking on your current call, their call will eventually stop ringing and they'll see a message indicating the call ended or wasn't answered.\n*   **\"Calling...\" (for a while):** Their screen may just display \"Calling...\" for a longer period than usual, before eventually failing.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **They won't explicitly see \"Busy.\"** WhatsApp doesn't use a \"Busy\" status like traditional phone lines.\n*   **The caller might assume you are busy.** The fact that the call wasn't answered implies you are unavailable.\n*   **Call Waiting (Maybe):** In some circumstances, and depending on your device and settings, the second caller might trigger a \"call waiting\" notification on your end, allowing you to either end the first call or ignore the second. This is not a fully reliable feature on WhatsApp.\n*   **Carrier Differences:** The specific behavior might vary slightly depending on the phone carrier and WhatsApp version.\n\nIn short, they won't get a direct \"busy\" signal, but the call will likely go unanswered and they'll likely assume you are on another call.\n",
